# GitHub Copilot Custom Agents Training

## Overview
Duration: 45:00
Topics: 5

---

## Section 1: Introduction to Custom Agents (8:30)

### What are Custom Agents?
- Custom agents extend GitHub Copilot with specialized behaviors
- Agents can have specific tools and instructions
- Available across multiple development environments

### Benefits
- Task-specific optimization
- Consistent behavior for specialized workflows
- Reusable configurations

---

## Section 2: Creating Your First Agent (12:15)

### File Structure (4:00)
- Use .agent.md extension
- YAML front matter configuration
- Markdown body for instructions

### Required Fields (3:30)
- name: Agent identifier
- description: Brief purpose statement
- tools: Available tool array
- model: AI model specification

### Agent Body Content (4:45)
- Write clear instructions
- Define agent role and expertise
- Specify behavioral guidelines
- Include examples

---

## Section 3: Configuring Agent Tools (9:20)

### Built-in Tools (4:10)
- read: Read file contents
- edit: Modify files
- search: Semantic code search
- github: GitHub operations
- terminal: Execute commands

### Custom Tool Selection (5:10)
- Restrict tools for security
- Grant minimal necessary permissions
- Consider agent purpose
- Test tool combinations

---

## Section 4: Advanced Features (10:45)

### Handoffs Between Agents (5:25)
- Define workflow transitions
- Pre-fill prompts for next agent
- Create guided multi-step processes
- Example: Planning → Implementation → Review

### Model Context Protocol (MCP) (5:20)
- Extend agents with external tools
- Configure MCP servers
- Organization-level capabilities
- Weather, database, API integrations

---

## Section 5: Best Practices and Deployment (4:10)

### Design Principles (2:00)
- Focus on single responsibility
- Use clear, actionable instructions
- Provide relevant examples
- Test thoroughly before deployment

### Distribution Options (2:10)
- Repository-level: .github/agents/
- Organization: agents/ (root)
- User profile: Personal agents
- Choose appropriate scope

